{"id":790,"date":"2022-01-16T16:58:53","date_gmt":"2022-01-16T16:58:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=790"},"modified":"2022-01-16T16:58:59","modified_gmt":"2022-01-16T16:58:59","slug":"use-looping-constructs-for-etc-to-process-file-command-line-input","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=790","title":{"rendered":"Use Looping constructs (for, etc.) to process file, command line input"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>Loops<\/strong> are among the most <strong>basic and powerful of programming concepts<\/strong>. A loop in a computer program is an instruction that repeats until a specified condition is reached. In a loop structure, the loop\u00a0asks a question. If the answer requires action, it is executed. The same question is asked again and again\u00a0until no further action is required. Each time the question is asked is called an iteration.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you can run UNIX command or task 5 times or read and process list of files using a for loop. A for loop can be used at a shell prompt or within a shell script itself.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"mntl-sc-block_1-0-6\">Types of Loops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul id=\"mntl-sc-block_1-0-7\"><li><strong>FOR LOOP<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>This type of for loop is characterized by counting<\/strong>. The range is specified by a beginning and ending number or item in the list. The for loop executes a sequence of commands for each member in a list of items. You can also use a range of numbers, as you can see in the picture on the right.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?resize=371%2C171&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-791\" width=\"371\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?w=364&amp;ssl=1 364w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-101.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 371px) 100vw, 371px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"402\" height=\"184\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?resize=402%2C184&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-792\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?w=402&amp;ssl=1 402w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-102.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The output of the script will still be the same<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"427\" height=\"171\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?resize=427%2C171&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-793\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?w=427&amp;ssl=1 427w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?resize=300%2C120&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-103.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 427px) 100vw, 427px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Real life use example<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s say you are in the situation where you need to all multiple new users and their password into the system, you could write a text file with their desired names and password and feed that file into the script which fill loops the command with input data<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignright size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"470\" height=\"184\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?resize=470%2C184&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-794\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?w=470&amp;ssl=1 470w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?resize=300%2C117&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-104.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 470px) 100vw, 470px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"356\" height=\"188\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?resize=356%2C188&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-796\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?w=356&amp;ssl=1 356w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?resize=24%2C13&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-106.png?resize=48%2C25&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"517\" height=\"168\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?resize=517%2C168&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-797\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?w=517&amp;ssl=1 517w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?resize=300%2C97&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-107.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 517px) 100vw, 517px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Or maybe you just want to get some data from multiple servers, you would maybe write something like this<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"563\" height=\"121\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?resize=563%2C121&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-799\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?w=563&amp;ssl=1 563w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?resize=300%2C64&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?resize=36%2C8&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-108.png?resize=48%2C10&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>WHILE LOOP<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>while<\/strong>&nbsp;executes a piece of code if the control expression is true, and only stops when it is false (or a explicit break is found within the executed code.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"365\" height=\"171\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?resize=365%2C171&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?w=365&amp;ssl=1 365w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-109.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 365px) 100vw, 365px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignright size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"402\" height=\"107\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?resize=402%2C107&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-801\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?w=402&amp;ssl=1 402w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?resize=300%2C80&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?resize=24%2C6&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-110.png?resize=48%2C13&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You maybe noticed few things that doesn&#8217;t make sense. The first is what in the pi is COUNTER++ and I would say, the keen eye you have there. The ++ it&#8217;s called incrementation which is one of many ways of gradually increasing or decreasing the value of our variable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another little thing could be what our counting has stopped at 4 even we wrote down 5. Why is that? Well in the programming world the counting always starts at 0, so together if you summarize the numbers you will get 5.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>UNTIL LOOP<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>until<\/strong>&nbsp;loop is almost equal to the while loop, except that the code is executed while the control expression evaluates to false.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you suspect that while and until are very similar, you are right.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"378\" height=\"162\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?resize=378%2C162&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-802\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?w=378&amp;ssl=1 378w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?resize=300%2C129&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-111.png?resize=48%2C21&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 378px) 100vw, 378px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignright size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"406\" height=\"127\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?resize=406%2C127&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-803\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?w=406&amp;ssl=1 406w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?resize=300%2C94&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-112.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 406px) 100vw, 406px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many more loops, but I think this is a good introduction to the whole looping concept and I don&#8217;t want you &#8220;loop your head around&#8221; if you know what I mean, so if you are interested I would highly suggest doing some sort of course for bash programming.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Loops are among the most basic and powerful of programming concepts. A loop in a [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":760,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[295,294,297,292,293],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-create-simple-shell-scripts-2.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/790"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=790"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/790\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":805,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/790\/revisions\/805"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/760"}],"wp:attach